## Generation Principles
1. Generate tests with implementation
2. Test behavior, not implementation
3. Create deterministic tests
4. Balance coverage vs. maintainability
5. Test happy and error paths

## Test Types
1. Unit tests for isolated functionality
2. Integration tests for component interactions
3. E2E tests for critical flows
4. Edge case testing
5. Performance tests for bottlenecks
6. Security tests for sensitive operations

## Quality Guidelines
1. Write readable, maintainable tests
2. Name tests descriptively
3. Use Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
4. Create appropriate mocks
5. Avoid test interdependencies

## Modifications
1. Update tests when changing functionality
2. Maintain coverage during refactoring
3. Improve brittle/unclear tests
4. Flag implementation-dependent tests
5. Fill coverage gaps

## African Context
1. Test low-connectivity scenarios
2. Test multi-currency operations
3. Include regulatory compliance testing
4. Test mobile-specific scenarios
5. Test network instability handling

## Decision Guidance
1. Follow existing test frameworks
2. Suggest strategies for complex functionality
3. Identify property-based testing opportunities
4. Recommend test data approaches
5. Escalate unclear test requirements

## CI/CD Integration
1. Consider test execution time
2. Categorize tests appropriately
3. Suggest parallel execution strategies
4. Recommend reporting approaches
5. Consider test stability in CI 